{"id":952365943,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"1Â month","timestamp":1684365037,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"93 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/952365943/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"16.5 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: Optional[ListNode], l2: Optional[ListNode]) -> Optional[ListNode]:\n\n        def lst2link(lst):\n            cur = dummy = ListNode(0)\n            for e in lst:\n                cur.next = ListNode(e)\n                cur = cur.next\n            return dummy.next\n\n        num1, num2 = [], []\n\n        while l1 != None:\n            num1.append(l1.val)\n            l1 = l1.next\n        \n        while l2 != None:\n            num2.append(l2.val)\n            l2 = l2.next\n        \n        num1 = ''.join((str(num1[num]) for num in range(len(num1))[::-1]))\n        num2 = ''.join((str(num2[num]) for num in range(len(num2))[::-1]))\n\n        total = int(num1) + int(num2)\n\n        total = [int(d) for d in str(total)[::-1]]\n\n        return lst2link(total)\n\n        \n            ","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false}
